#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/community/_index.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Community"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:7
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Whether it be to solve a problem or to contribute in any way, the Xfce "
"communities are a good place to get help or to share your ideas. You might "
"also want to have a look at the communities of the different distributions "
"which provide Xfce.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:8
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Mailing lists"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:11
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Almost all development and coordination work is taking place on the Xfce "
"mailing lists. A summary of all lists is available at "
"[mail.xfce.org](https://mail.xfce.org). There is also a user-specific list "
"where you can ask questions and freely discuss about the desktop.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:13
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**NOTE:** In order to post to these lists, you must first subscribe.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:14
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Matrix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:17
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have a problem that you cannot resolve, you might want to try asking "
"a question in our Matrix channel "
"[#xfce](https://matrix.to/#/#xfce:matrix.org). The channel has several "
"active users. It is recommended that you consult the "
"[documentation](https://docs.xfce.org/) about your problem before asking "
"your question.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:18
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Forums"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:21
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For users who prefer forums, the [Xfce Forum](https://forum.xfce.org/) is "
"the place to be. Active contributors will be able to help you, but please do "
"not use it for bug reports.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/community/_index.md:22
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Social Networks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/community/_index.md:24
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can follow us on the official [Mastodon "
"account](https://floss.social/@xfce) or [Twitter "
"account](https://twitter.com/xfceofficial)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/_index.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "About"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:7
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Xfce is a lightweight desktop environment for UNIX-like operating "
"systems. It aims to be fast and low on system resources, while still being "
"visually appealing and user friendly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:9
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Xfce embodies the traditional UNIX philosophy of modularity and "
"re-usability. It consists of a number of components that provide the full "
"functionality one can expect of a modern desktop environment. They are "
"packaged separately and you can pick among the available packages to create "
"the optimal personal working environment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:11
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Another priority of Xfce is adherence to standards, specifically those "
"defined at [freedesktop.org](https://freedesktop.org).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:13
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Xfce can be installed on several UNIX platforms. It is known to compile on "
"Linux, NetBSD, FreeBSD, OpenBSD, Solaris, Cygwin and MacOS X, on x86, PPC, "
"Sparc, Alpha...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/_index.md:14
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:17
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Xfce contains a number of core components for the minimum tasks you'd expect "
"from a desktop environment:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:18
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Window Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:21
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Manages the placement of windows on the screen, provides window decorations "
"and manages workspaces or virtual desktops.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:22
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Desktop Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:25
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Sets the background image and provides a root window menu, desktop icons or "
"minimized icons and a windows list.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:26
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Panel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:29
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Switch between opened windows, launch applications, switch workspaces and "
"menu plugins to browse applications or directories.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:30
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Session Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:33
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Controls the login and power management of the desktop and allows you to "
"store multiple login sessions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:34
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Application Finder"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:37
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Shows the applications installed on your system in categories, so you can "
"quickly find and launch them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:38
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "File Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:41
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Provides the basic file-management features and unique utilities like the "
"bulk renamer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/_index.md:42
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Settings Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/about/_index.md:45
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Tools to control the various settings of the desktop; like keyboard "
"shortcuts, appearance, display settings, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/_index.md:46
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Beside the basic set of modules, Xfce also provides numerous additional "
"applications and plugins so you can extend your desktop the way you like, "
"for example a terminal emulator, text editor, sound mixer, application "
"finder, image viewer, iCal based calendar and a CD and DVD burning "
"application. You can read more about the modules of Xfce in the "
"[projects](/projects) page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Get Involved"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:7
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Welcome to the Xfce community. By joining our team, you will be part of an "
"international effort by hundreds of people working to deliver a stunning "
"Free Software computing experience. You will meet new friends, learn new "
"skills and make a difference to millions of users while working with people "
"from all around the globe. There are many different ways you can become part "
"of this, just read on and pick an area which interests you or seems "
"challenging.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:9
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Possible tasks include testing, bug reporting; writing code, developing "
"artwork, documentation or translations; or spreading the word and helping "
"out with promotion and marketing both on line and at tradeshows and "
"conferences.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:10
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:13
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There's lots of people using and testing Xfce. By providing useful and "
"up-to-date documentation, you will make a big impact on helping people "
"understand how to make the most of the Xfce Desktop Environment. [Learn More "
"→](https://docs.xfce.org/contribute/documentation)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:14
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Translation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:17
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Are you fluent in multiple languages? By contributing your translations of "
"text to the Xfce Desktop Environment, you will help Xfce be a better part of "
"the global market and more accessible to the millions of potential users out "
"there. [Learn More →](https://docs.xfce.org/contribute/translate/start)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:18
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Development"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:21
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"By becoming a developer, you can make a big difference while enjoying a "
"challenging and fun experience. You'll learn to be a better coder, you will "
"get to implement new features and defeat daunting bugs, creating a stunning "
"product, all the while collaborating with people from all around the "
"world. You can start by browsing the [source "
"code](https://gitlab.xfce.org).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:22
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Promotion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:25
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you own a blog or website you can greatly help by spreading the word and "
"encouraging new users to give Xfce a try. If you have a Mastodon or Twitter "
"account you can also help by reposting any announcements we make to help us "
"reach a larger audience.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:26
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Bug Reporting and testing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:29
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"One of the most useful tasks that we rely on the community for is testing "
"and reporting of bugs. Since Xfce runs on various platform and in a lot of "
"different setups, testing all changes in every possible situation is an "
"impossible task. As such we kindly ask users to assist in testing, and "
"reporting all bugs they may find, using our [bug "
"tracker](https://gitlab.xfce.org).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:31
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once a bug has been found, the cause of the bug needs to be tracked down, "
"and then (obviously) fixed. If you want to get involved in the actual "
"development process of Xfce a great way to start is by solving bugs and then "
"submitting a patch file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:32
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "OpenCollective"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/getinvolved/_index.md:34
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to fund the project, you can use OpenCollective. Xfce has "
"created two collectives, known as [Xfce "
"($)](https://opencollective.com/xfce) and [Xfce-Eu "
"(€)](https://opencollective.com/xfce-eu) respectively. [Learn More "
"→](https://mail.xfce.org/pipermail/xfce/2021-May/037348.html)\n"
msgstr ""
